t bedroom can add more than 20% to the value of a property.&rdquo;</span></span><br style="color: rgb(45, 45, 45); font-family: arial; font-size: 16.8px; text-align: justify;" />\n	<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/money/2011/may/03/loft-conversions-biggest-boost-house-values" rel="noopener" style="color: rgb(0, 85, 150); text-decoration-line: none; font-family: arial; font-size: 16.8px; text-align: justify;" target="_blank">The Guardian</a></span></p>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;">Brief History about Harrow&nbsp;</span></h3>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London_Borough_of_Harrow">Harrow</a> is Home to the exclusive Harrow School on the Hill and with the <a href="https://londonist.com/london/secret/things-you-didn-t-know-about-the-borough-of-harrow">London Borough of Harrow</a>, it is the perfect blending of the leafy, affluent area of Harrow on the Hill and the conventional semi-detached properties and flats of a North West London Borough. &nbsp;With its low crime figures and high proportion of greenbelt land, Harrow is a very popular location for both families and affluent singles who are looking for a safe, clean environment in which to live just a stones throw from central London.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Why Luxury Loft Conversion in Harrow?</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/">Loft conversions</a> are very popular in Harrow as families seek to maximize their living space in an area that has enjoyed great prosperity. Properties that are being marketed in Harrow have accompanying planning permission to convert the loft. This is a good sign indicating the popularity of loft conversions in Harrow.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Whether your residence is in Harrow-on-the-Hill, or <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/loft-conversion-pinner">Pinner</a> or <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/loft-conversion-stanmore">Stanmore</a>, whether it is the in the attic or bedroom, loft conversion always provides you dividends. You would be pleased with a place of retreat at the top of the house and following a long hectic day in the office, enjoy the serenity and silent atmosphere in a room separated from rest of the house.</span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_78631.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	Why Loft Conversions are best for Harrow Residents?&nbsp;</h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">At Loft Conversion London, we understand that extensions are not always the best ways to create space and are not cost-effective either. Loft conversion on the other hand is the best way to increase your internal living space without really spending too much. Our dedicated team member will ensure all the assessments are undertaken before commencing the work so that we adhere to all building regulations and architecture drawing from start to finish. Whether you want a <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/dormer-loft-conversion">Dormer</a>, <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/hip-to-gable-loft-conversions">Gable</a>, <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/velux-loft-conversion">Velux </a>or <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/mansard-loft-conversion">Mansard Loft Conversion</a>, we will make sure your Loft is completed perfectly to suit your requirements.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;">What are the benefits of Converting your Loft in Harrow?&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">The prime benefit of undertaking a Loft Conversion to your house is &quot; <em><strong>adding considerable value to your house</strong></em>&quot;. In Harrow, a house that has a luxury loft conversion will sell for more then 20% than similar houses without loft conversions. The cost of the loft conversion is relatively little in comparision to what your house will sell later on. All in all, if you end up selling your house in Harrow, then you will have some extra money from the Loft conversion in your house. </span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;">Here at Loft Conversion London, we are dedicated at what we do, our workmanship is second to none and we employ some of the best tradesmen whose experience in unparalled in the loft conversion industry. We understand that undertaking a full loft conversion in your harrow home can be a major disruption, however we will ensure the whole process is run as smoothly as possible from day 1 till completion.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;">We cover all areas in the Harrow region, <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/loft-conversion-stanmore">Stanmore</a>, <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/loft-conversion-hatchend">Hatch end</a>, <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/loft-conversion-pinner">Pinner</a>, <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/loft-conversion-edgware">Edgware</a> and many more. Contact us for any enquiries.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>What Things to Consider before undertaking a Loft Conversion?</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Of all parts of your house, the loft stands as one of the easiest and least troublesome space to convert into a more meaningful and useful room. Moving to a bigger place is stressful and expensive that will disrupt your normal life, as well as, you&rsquo;re your family. According to a report filed by the <a href="https://www.rics.org/uk/">Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors</a> (RICS), it was revealed that loft conversion is just <em><strong>one third the cost of moving to a bigger property</strong></em>. It is also profitable as loft conversion increases the value of your current home by as much as 25%.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow1.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Head height - Do you have adequate height for a loft in Harrow?&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">A potential room in the loft needs a height clearance so that the measurement from the highest point of the roof to the floor should be a minimum of 2.3 meters. To make the space habitable make sure that the loft space in your Harrow house must have the height as stated by the local building regulations.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Strengthening the roof and floor</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Consider the structure of the loft conversion. In some instances, you need to provide more strengthening for your loft by using steel beams to underpin the floor and roof itself. This will be required if the structure of your house is deemed weak by the structural engineer. It is for your safety and the durability of the house that roofs and floors are strengthened.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Loft staircase</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">The Law stipulated that any loft conversion must have its own permanent separate staircase. However, stairs must be provided for a loft conversion to fit the measurement of the area allocated but it does not need to follow the width of the steps on lower flights in the home. Make sure the landing of the loft has enough space for head clearance.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Use natural light</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Loft needs lots of natural light. One option is to install roof/velux windows or skylights so there will be more lights and extra ventilation to the room. Use skylight access for a fully open roof window to provide not only natural light but also a point of access to a roof terrace or other outdoor roof space. This is a cost effective thing to do and it reduces your electricity bill in the long run.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">About planning permission</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Not all loft conversions require a planning permission as the rules were relaxed way back October 2008. But to be sure. check before carrying out any serious work. However, if your dormer or Velux windows are in the front of the property then you will need planning permission. Anything that alters the roof will require planning permission.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Raise the property value</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Believe us when we say that loft extensions increase the value of a property. Not just 5 or 10% but the increase goes up to 20% after loft conversions. So, you might want to think about that because the rates of the property are never decreasing but they are always increasing with every passing year.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Some frequently asked questions about Loft Conversions in Harrow?</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">As usual, we always share with you the questions and answers included in our Loft report.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">1. Is the headroom of my Loft enough for Conversion?</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Most lofts are convertible, but an achievable headroom is needed to be at least 2.3 meter or 7 feet 6 inches to start with from the existing ceiling joists way down to the apex of the loft; however, a slightly less height would still be fine.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">2. Is Loft conversion affordable? How much will the average Loft conversion cost?</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">To answer this question, the company must look at property that is why we offer a free, fully detailed and all-inclusive loft conversion quote which we post to you soon after carrying out a survey; it costs nothing to find out!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">But the typical cost of loft conversions starts around &pound;24,000 and can head up to anywhere in the region of &pound;60,000 depending on the property and the scale of the work. See the infographic below which showcases the value Loft Conversion adds to your house. Source <a href="https://www.comparemymove.com/chartered-surveyors/adding-value-to-your-home">Comparemymove</a></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-value.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 408px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">3. What is your timetable for the conversion?</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">The time depends on the type of loft conversion but typically it takes:</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">5 to 7 weeks - <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/velux-loft-conversion">Velux Loft Conversion</a></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_67131.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/velux-loft-conversion.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">6 to 7 weeks - <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/dormer-loft-conversion">Dormer Loft Conversion</a>.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_56665.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/flat-roof-loft-conversion.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">7 to 8 weeks -<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/l-shaped-dormer-loft-conversion"> L-shaped Dormer Loft Conversion</a></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_84463.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/L-shaped-loft-conversion.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">7 to 8 weeks - <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/hip-to-gable-loft-conversions">Hip to gable Loft Conversion</a></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_79531.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/hiptogable-loft-conversion.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">8 to 9 weeks - Hip to gable w/rear dormer.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/gabled-dormer-loft-conversion.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/mansard-loft-conversion">Mansard Loft Conversion</a> -8 to 10 weeks</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/mansard-loft-conversion.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Pitched Roof Loft Conversion - 8 to 10 weeks</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/pitched-roof-loft-conversion.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">4. What guarantee does your company give?</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Our company will stipulate the number of years warranty in the quote.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">5. Will my new room need smoke detectors?</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Our electricians follow Building Regulations regarding the use of interlinked smoke detectors placed at each level to comply with fire regulations. These main hard-wired smoke alarms keep a backup standby battery power supply.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">6. What more preparations can I do before my Loft Conversion?</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">You are now ready to start your project so get in touch with us to arrange a no obligation, feasibility study to determine the practicality and options for your loft conversion.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Now that you have all the info about loft conversion in Harrow, you can begin your project with the help of our company, Enjoy your new loft.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;">Here is an example of a Loft Conversion we undertook in Harrow recently. This was a hip to gable and a rear dormer loft conversion. We added a master bedroom for our client finished to the highest standard. We can arrange viewings for you to see our properties that we have worked in Harrow and West London.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow3.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 338px;" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow5.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow6.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow-balcony.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow-bathroom.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-harrow-bedroom.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 22px;">Some useful links for you to read on before starting your Loft Conversion.</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/loft-conversion-ideas-to-choose-from"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Loft Conversion Ideas to Choose From</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/do-you-need-planning-permission-for-your-loft-conversion"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Do you need planning permission for your Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://www.which.co.uk/reviews/loft-conversions/article/loft-conversions/loft-conversions-step-by-step-guide"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Step by Step Guide to Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n', '', 'Loft Conversion Harrow | Harrow Loft Conversions Company                                                                                                                                                                 