(31, 'Loft Conversion Ruislip', 'Full Design to Build Service', '<strong>Are you Looking for a Loft Conversion in Ruislip?</strong>', 'Loft Conversions Company in Ruislip, North London', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">\n	<strong>Ruislip Loft Conversions&nbsp;</strong></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Ruislip is located in West London, England, about 13.8 miles (22.2 km) west-north-west of Charing Cross, London. This ancient Greater London ecclesiastical parish lay in the historic county of Middlesex. The parish is prominent as it used to appear in the Domesday Book and is today designated as local heritage site. Dating back in the 13<sup>th</sup> century, St Martin, its parish church is still being used by the people for religious activities.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">There building congregating at the northern end of Ruislip High Street used to be the core of the original village square and are now Grade II listed. Originally, it as a central water pump but it was moved out of the road in the 1970s due traffic increased.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Everyone living in Ruislip seems to love this area because it is serene, quiet and provides easy underground links to travel anywhere into central London. It is a peaceful suburb with a family-friendly outlook.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/ruislip-high-street.jpg" style="width: 560px; height: 315px;" /></span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Did you Know Four out of 10 homes in All boroughs have Loft Conversions?</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Many people believe in the saying that you don&rsquo;t have to be rich to turn the property you love into the home of your dreams. But this did not only happen to Ruislip but all over the other boroughs in London. <strong>Do you know that for every 10 homes in many areas of London, 4 have undergone a Loft conversion?</strong> A new research revealed that the London boroughs with the highest value of property and most number of homes had loft conversions for the last five years.These includes many residences on the boroughs inside and outside Greater London.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">In Ruislip, our Loft Conversion Company has years of experience in creating loft spaces into any living space &ndash; it could be a new bedroom, bathroom or a home cinema, office or whatever else might capture the imagination of the owner.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_13370.jpg" style="width: 492px; height: 640px;" /></span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Only the best service from our Loft Conversion</strong> <strong>Company in Ruislip</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Our company believed that there must be close contact between clients and company, as well as the important role of communication, resiliency, and assistance that are possessed by our supervisors and building teams. We know pretty well that we are working in your home that you are proud of and we will do our part. We try as much as possible to minimize the disruption, mess, and noise due to the loft conversion work.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">With loft conversions starting from just the cost of &pound;20</span><span style="font-size: 22px;">,000, you will be living in a more spacious and enjoyable home with your family.</span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Why opt for Loft Conversion in Ruislip</strong>?</span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">It is an acknowledged fact that loft conversions are the best way to add value to your home &ndash; as they add an entire new floor,&nbsp; increase total square footage, added to the number of rooms and new bathrooms, in general, a more spacious home is created. And more often, no planning permit is needed. So do not wait longer to enjoy that lovely home! In most cases, the loft at home is kept idle as a place for things unused and wasted that you throw out in the junk. So consider contacting our experts from Ruislip to convert that empty space into a magical space according to your requirements. Do not worry about the cost for it could be less than you think, so inquire from our company.</span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Some important considerations before you start!</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Although loft conversions appears to be easy and simple requiring the usual work, you might be tempted to save money by DIY. Don&rsquo;t ever think you can do it yourself sunce numerous elements are involved that requires the work of an expert.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">First, there&rsquo;s the structural element to consider for lofts are build to support the roof to stay up and preserve the structual soundness of the house. So do not bother house structurally sound, so do not touch the layout and setup for you might cause disaster..</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Often popular is the bungalow lot conversion for they increase floor space 2 times. However, they cannot bear &nbsp;second load-bearing floor inside and the structure becomes dangerous if it is done properly.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Insulation is an important factor to consider since internal walls and roofs are not the same and vary the way they are insulated. Plan carefully how you climb up to your new floor; otherwise, you will be using a ladder. Think of a better way to install a loft ladder which is not easy.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">There is also the important task of installing the skylights or the more difficult task of installing the dormer windows.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Once you have studies the many types of loft conversion ideas and you want obe in your home, contact us immediately in Ruislip, Greater London so that you get to know all requirements, the price and other details.</span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>What are the different types of Loft Conversions</strong>?</span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Loft conversions vary depending on the type of house and roof you have, how it has been constructed and how much space you want.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">1. <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/velux-loft-conversion">Velux</a> (Roof Light)</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">A Velux does not change original shape of your loft so you will only need small alterations for the roof to fit and help keep the cost to a minimum while helping you discover your dream space. One advantage of Velux is its versatility. More information about velux will be explained by our specialists.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/velux-loft-conversion-bedroom.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2. <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/dormer-loft-conversion">Dormers</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Dormer reshapes the roof to give greater internal height and space; there are many different styles but in most cases. the rear of the roof or the let side is the location of loft conversion. Although Velux windows provide extra natural light, but in general, the dormer conversions are popular all over the UK. This is because they offer excellent head room height, and good amount of space in general. Large dormers offer the most benefits and more value for money.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_49468.jpg" style="width: 259px; height: 194px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3. <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/hip-to-gable-loft-conversions">Hip to Gable</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">With the hip of your existing roof extended into a Gable end, greater roof space is given that allows a larger rear dormer to be constructed while maximizing your interior space. Hip to gables look more physically attractive than dormer conversions. A rear dormer loft conversion and a hip to gable loft conversion can be combined with the best results. This type of loft conversion is most popular in traditional homes.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_17748.jpg" style="width: 554px; height: 415px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">4. <a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/mansard-loft-conversion">Mansard</a></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">This type of loft conversion is similar to a flat roof dormer, with a front slope of&nbsp; about 70 degrees as the main difference. Windows look more aesthetically pleasing in a Mansard Conversion when it appears like small dormers. The benefits provided by the Mansard conversion is all that extra space. Almost as if the property as extra room when you raise one side of the pitched, the attic space transformed immediately into a roomy living area.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Of the different type, the Dormer loft conversions are the most popular style of loft conversion as they provide additional head room and floor space.Normally sitting at the back of the conversion, they served as an extension beyond the existing roof line and normally sit at the rear of the conversion.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/mansard-loft-conversion-london.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>These are your Benefits of Having a Loft Conversion in your Ruislip Home</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">1. You create more extra space</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">You realized that you need an extra space at home and have started considering buying a new house for this problem. However, you overlook the fact that your loft is vacant and you can use the space wisely. Yes, loft conversion is a good option to create an extra space you will be able to use practically in terms of your need. This additional space will also also solve the problam of storage faced by the different rooms of your home.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">2. The value of your property is increased</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Believe in our words that thed value of your property will be raised by a loft extensions and mind you, the increase is not merely the amount of 5% to 10% but it can be more since house value increases as much as 20% after loft conversions. Remember thaat realestate property never decrease but they are always increasing from year to year.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Now that if you think converting a loft is a good investment then find the best construction company in your vicinity for getting the best results.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">3. More storage areas</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Like I said above, extra space is very caluable as they becomes available can be used for many purpose as storing the items coming from different corners of your house. When the not-so-important items stored on the loft space, your house becomes an easy to walk around and relax as there are n more furniture item blocking your way.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-