ages/temp/full/gallery_soft_67131.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2. Dormer loft conversions in Ealing are the most popular option as lights are easily added and increasing the amount of roof space will offer a full headroom. To add a bigger box dormer with flat roof, they changed the sides or rear of roof structure of the house.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_56665.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3. The most commonly found on the side of either end-terrace or semi-detached houses is the hip-to-gable conversion. By removing the hipped or sloping side of the roof; the end wall is built up straight to form a new vertical gable.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_14248.jpg" style="width: 492px; height: 640px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">4. A new box extension is included in the loft conversion of a Gable-to-gable loft is the space spanning between each gable end. It is better to increase the length of the gable end walls to act like &lsquo;bookends&rsquo;.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_59330.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">5. The Mansard loft conversions in your Ealing house will create new volume. To complete the process, replace either one or both of your roof slopes with sloping sides that are extremely steep and over the top place a flat roof.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_