22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/velux-loft-conversion-bedroom.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2. The most popular type is the loft conversions called dormer that offers double advantages: easy way to add more lights and achieve a full headroom by increasing the roof space. To have a bigger flat-roofed &lsquo;box&rsquo; dormer, change the roof structure at the sides or back of the house.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_56665.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3. Usually found on the side of either end-terrace or semi-detached houses is the loft conversion called hip-to-gable. Removing the hipped (or sloping) side of the roof, a new vertical gable is formed when the end wall is built up straight.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_36859.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">4. A new box extension is included in this gable-to-gable loft conversion that spans the space in-between each gable end. To act like bookends, you need to lengthen the height of the gable end walls.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">5. If you need extra volume, Mansard loft conversion is your type. The process is quite complication as the sides are very steep and sloping while over the top flat roof is placed.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_82593.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 300px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">6. When the existing loft space is not adopted for conversion, use the modular extension loft conversions. The new room measurements are taken and a modular loft is manufactured off site and delivered to the house as a module. For installation, the existing roof must be removed,</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>There are versatile ways to utilize your converted loft:</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Create your own stylish loft bathroom.</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Bulky beams with awkward dimensions have very limiting factor but they be used to create a bathroom in an available loft space. The shower might require an amount of headroom and an easy entry, a bath can be constructed under a low ceiling. Utilized plain and simple shapes, as well as, the usual color palette for it complements period architecture. You can depend on your reliable loft roof to become a usable space with a stairway as access. Imagine the extra bedroom with a modern bathroom, or study or workroom you always wanted in the loft that could turn out to be the best and most spacious room in the house, a place you will be proud of.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-london-bathroom3.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Your very own home office</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">If do not need an extra sleeping quarter in the loft and a new sleeping area is not your family needs, but decide to work from home, then a home office might be the best use for your converted loft. To maximize productivity and produce more work, your home office must have lots of natural light. Refrain from using those black-out blinds and heavy dark solid drapes. Instead, opt for pale blinds as pink, light blue and neutral shades that allow entry of natural light in but at the same time minimize the glare. Light is necessary during the summer months, as well as, during the winter months when cold days are shorter.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/home-office-hillingdon.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Loft conversion for kids</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Your kids will laud you for giving them the loft as their very own space with no mommy watching their activities. They can even decorate the room themselves, but it must be cozy with lots of light and air. Children&rsquo;s room must be filled with light and bright colors. Kids must be encouraged to express their personality using colors, decors soft furnishings and other accessories.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Your loft conversion dressing room</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Now you have your own dressing room after you made use of the space in the eaves with built in storage that helps to overcome the limitations of an awkward sloping roof. The large skylight floods the space with natural light, while the proper position of your floorboards will give you the appearance of a longer space. How about tacking a wardrobe onto the side of a large master bedroom?</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Your walk &ndash; in closet</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Movie stars are proud of their walk-in closet that they proudly show off in the magazines. Why not create one for you? This would be a good idea to use your loft conversion. Since your space is inadequate but plan to create a walk-in closet into your loft conversion, opt an open-type wardrobe or a clothes rack to maximize the space you want. You can use the rack to show your collection of bags, shoes and other items of interest.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/frontend/main/feature_66488.jpg" style="width: 300px; height: 158px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Space for fitting and storage</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">If you are looking for a space to store useful articles safely, then use your converted loft. Just be sure to make the most of space that might otherwise have been wasted by proper placement of those items. One day when stored items are gone, you think of more ways to use your converted apace.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/frontend/main/feature_14464.jpg" style="width: 281px; height: 210px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Facts you should know before starting conversion</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">1: Consider the area where you live with people having homes with loft conversions. These lofts are well- executed most of them using ecologically friendly materials that will greatly benefit the environment of the area.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2: A bathroom made from loft conversion is practical and affordable that easily fits the space in the loft. Sometimes, plumbing or water tank is necessary, but you can find a way in supplying water in your loft.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3: Planning permission may not be needed for the in 2008, legislation on permit development ruled that any extension not beyond 2 storeys does not need a permit as long as they are within the limitations set by the legislation. Consider your house and the area as well as your property. Buildings are subjected to far more regulations.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">4: Loft conversions are not only affordable but need shorter time to complete than extensions. Just consider a dormer conversion, it requires 4 weeks but not more than 6 weeks for completion. But when the size is bigger and the style more complicated, then more time is needed.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">5. All types of homes can have their lofts converted whether it is a mansion with its elaborate Victorian terrace or a small bungalow for two, there will always be a style of loft conversion made fit exactly what you need.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">6. Loft conversions are becoming popular and a favorite in most households they fit the family need, as well as, their budget. Whether it is conversion for a larger family unit or for just a powder room for Madame, an extra room for hobbies and entertaining, loft conversions continue to be both economically and practically a good option.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Now that you know everything about loft conversion, you can start your project. You will not do it alone as we will be with you all the way. For your free estimate or for more information on the loft, call us anytime for free quote; we are just a click away!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 22px;">Some useful links for you to read on before starting your Loft Conversion.</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/loft-conversion-ideas-to-choose-from"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Loft Conversion Ideas to Choose From</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/do-you-need-planning-permission-for-your-loft-conversion"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Do you need planning permission for your Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://www.which.co.uk/reviews/loft-conversions/article/loft-conversions/loft-conversions-step-by-step-guide"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Step by Step Guide to Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n', '', 'Loft Conversion Kingston | Kingston Loft Conversions Company                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            ', 'Looking for a Loft Conversion Company in Kingston? We undertake all loft conversion work in Kingston right from design to build. Contact our team today for a free estimate and site survey                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   ', 'loft conversion kingston', 'loft-conversion-kingston', NULL, 1, '1', '1', 0, '', '', '2019-11-08'),
(45, 'Loft Conversion Teddington', 'Full Design to Build Service', '<strong>Looking to Convert your Loft in Teddington?</strong>', 'Loft Conversions Company in Teddington, South London', '<h1>\n	Teddington Loft Conversions</h1>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Where is Teddington Located?&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Teddington is an upper-class borough located along South West riverside in London. You can find this borough along the river part of the Thames in the midst of Hampton Wick, Strawberry Hill, and Twickenham.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Homes are mostly residential stretching from the river to Bushy Park along high streets lined up with market shops, pubs, and restaurants. You find at the lowest non-tidal lock on the Thames a suspension bridge overlooking the Thames, Teddington Lock. Filled with apartments and offices, this mid-rise urban is found at the center of Teddington&#39;s development. House prices in Teddington and its surrounding areas are among the highest outside of Central London.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Living in Teddington</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">As one of the boroughs, we consider this green and pleasant land of Victorian streets and good commuter links as the best in-between option for families who are bothered by the hassle and buzzle of the big city but find quiet country life too serious. In the meantime, iconic film studios that were converted into flats have brought levels of luxury in the area.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Typical house buyers are young couple with kids since this place is a child-friendly environment with green parks, river, and good schools. Building boom in Teddington happened in the Victorian and Edwardian eras so most houses were built had terraces. Transport is easy as it is a commuter suburb after railways arrived in Teddington as early as 1863.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Interesting facts about Teddington</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">1.Teddington has been the home of film studios that was operated for many years by the Pinewood Studios Group. However, in the late era, the owners decided to demolish the complex and build new housing.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2.Teddington can claim to be the home of modern hockey. It was in 1861 that Teddington Hockey Club developed many playing styles and rules that are now ubiquitous with the modern game.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3. The National Physical Laboratory that set up national standards and units of measurement was then located in Bushy Park. The place hosted the visit of several dignitaries like Prime Minister Lord North and the soon-to-be William IV.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Loft Conversion in Teddington</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">This is one of the loveliest locations in London for it provides many fine opportunities, as well as a host of happy neighbors, plus the advantage of being a healthy place to raise a family or start a new life. However, one hard task for homeowners is to find space for all the things that have compiled in their lifetime. Some homeowners living in the Teddington area complained about the limitation of their space. With the coming of loft conversion, the problem of place was no longer a great issue by the presence of our Teddington loft conversions.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/Windsor-avenue-hillingdon.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Having Loft Conversions are easy in Teddington</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Thanks to our loft conversion company, Teddington has an all-inclusive team of experts to get the job done. For you will find an easy solution for this problem. With conversion, you can have more space and storage without breaking your bank and create chaos in your household.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">With our expertise for several decades, we can get the job done. Whatever is your aim or idea for the loft, we will make sure you can get all the help that you need to set it up. With our loft conversion, you will be able to make quick changes for what you want and when you want to make the change. You could have everything from an extra bathroom to a new bedroom &ndash; completed based on your timeline.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/velux-loft-conversion-london.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Finding the right Loft Conversion for you</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">A good quality loft conversion is like hitting 2 birds with a single stone: you will gain not only an additional living space also increase the value of your home. Nationwide conducted a study and revealed that up to 20% to 25% is added to your home value. A great investment, indeed!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">There are 4 main types the Loft Conversions you can choose from:</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">1. The Mansard is like a flat roof dormer with the only difference of the 70 degrees front slopes. The advantages are: no requirement for structural reinforcement and does not require much in the way of structural reinforcements;</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_82593.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 300px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">and they are easier to furnish than lofts with slanted roots due to their straight walls.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2. Hip to Gable widens into a Gable end the hip of the existing roof as it increases the size of the room. You not only save money, but you also add value to your existing home. &nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_36859.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3. Dormer is basically extending what protrudes from the slope of the roof. It is cost effective in maximizing space can be added to any side of a house. However, planning permission is required in most cases.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_56665.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">4. Velux is loft conversion without changing the shape of the roof. It is both time and money saver. In the Velux loft conversion, you don&rsquo;t need planning permission, and you just put in the windows to the property.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/velux-loft-conversion-bedroom.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Essential considerations for your Loft Conversion in Teddington</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Loft stairs</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">The ideal scenario is for your stairs to start from an existing stairwell using a domer or some other extension if not enough headroom is found for the flight of stairs to land in the attic.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/windsor-avenue-staircases.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Strengthening floor joists</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">It is important to strengthen floor by adding stable joists immediately beside the old ones or inserting in-between. Sometimes. you will be using thicker than the current ones to raise the height of the floor.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-company-london.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Loft insulation &amp; ventilation</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">For better comfortable living, upgrade the insulation at rafter level that is usually done by inserting stiff insulation in the midst and below the rafters, by leaving a 50 mm void in between the existing roof&rsquo;s underside of to increase ventilation.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/frontend/main/feature_57263.jpg" style="width: 280px; height: 210px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Loft sound proofing</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">To tackle the problem of noise, consider the fabric of your roof &ndash; such as using a ceiling plasterboard for and for party walls), or apply glazing products that deaden the sound. To bat the noise. be sure to ensuring good airtightness.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Plumbing &amp; electrics</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Always check the electrical appliances in your lost if central heating and electrical systems have enough power to supply the new space as well as their distribution the area that they are needed. Do the same with the plumbing.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Fire safety for loft conversions</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Every building must have a safe means of escape in case of fire and the standard provision of escape windows on every floor. A new space at home from a conversion needs a protected stairway leading down to the main exit in case of emergency.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Benefits of undertaking a Loft conversion in your Teddington Home</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">1. You have all the extra space that you need.</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">An extra space is needed and have started considering buying a new house for its solution. However, you overlook the existence of your &nbsp;vacant loft and you can see its potential use. Yes, loft conversion is a good option to create an extra space you will be able to use practically in terms of your need. This additional space also solves the problem of storage faced by the different rooms of your home.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-london-bathroom.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">2. The value of your property is increased &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Believe that the value of your property will be raised by a loft extension and its increased is not 5% to 10% but even more since house value increases as much as 20% after loft conversions. Remember that real estate property never decreases but they are always increasing from year to year.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">3. Many more storage areas</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Like I have always maintained that extra space is very valuable as they can be used by many households for storing the items coming from different corners of your house. When the not-so-important items have found a place on the loft space, your house becomes clean and provide an easy to walk around and relax area as the unused furniture are properly stored eliminating any block along the way.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/frontend/main/feature_14464.jpg" style="width: 281px; height: 210px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Benefit of natural lights for Loft Conversion</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Your loft conversion is a great way to increase the natural light inside your home. Light reveals the true potential of your new home space, which will in turn help to make your house more desirable and have an impact on its value.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">More natural light from your loft can also transform a dark area of your home into a place for the whole family to bond. Add a roof windows to convert your loft onto a playroom or wish to build a sunroom where you can get away in the afternoons your loft conversion</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/frontend/main/feature_70373.jpg" style="width: 300px; height: 200px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Ideas for lighting your loft conversion</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Loft conversion is a process where you transform an empty attic space of your house into a room depending on its height and width. It can be used as a spare bedroom, home office, personal gym or additional storage space depending on your need.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">You can plan the lighting of loft conversion into something special that will give it a lift and changes the whole mood of the room providing positive aura. So, plan well the lighting of your conversion according to the options available in your loft space and the trends that are popular all over UK.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Low light ceilings</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Generally, lights in the ceilings of the loft conversion are very low and there are wide variety of lights in London to choose from. Choose lights that just hang from the ceilings and do not acquire much space and head room as well. They are beautiful and let it match with your home decor.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Lights on walls</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">You can choose from various designs of wall lights that are available in the London market to match up with your loft conversion. You are free to put enough lights on the walls so all dark corners will have lights if the loft is your bedroom, light up in the center to highlight your bed.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">LED spot lighting</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">LED light is user friendly and economical on your budget as well. They are available in a wide range of designs and consume less power. You can set them as per different patterns that will set the ambience and mood of the room.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Sensored lighting</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">For convenience and energy, lights are operated through a sensor that is a great option for loft conversions. Lights will turn up automatically when you will enter the room and they will turn off when you will leave the room.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Natural light</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">You can put a large window on the roof with blinds that will also stop too much light to enter the loft room. When you want to light up your room, use natural light by opening the blinds or open the windows for some fresh air.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">Table lamps</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">If you are using the loft space just for the sleeping purpose, then you do not want a flashy light for this room. Instead of installing LED and wall lights, you can buy a compact table lamp that will be more than enough to take care of your loft room.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Our company will be behind you from the star of planning your conversion until you enjoy the extra space. Sit down and relax and let us do the rest!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 22px;">Some useful links for you to read on before starting your Loft Conversion.</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/loft-conversion-ideas-to-choose-from"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Loft Conversion Ideas to Choose From</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/do-you-need-planning-permission-for-your-loft-conversion"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Do you need planning permission for your Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://www.which.co.uk/reviews/loft-conversions/article/loft-conversions/loft-conversions-step-by-step-guide"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Step by Step Guide to Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n', '', 'Loft Conversion Teddington | Teddington Loft Conversions Company                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            ', 'Looking for a Loft Conversion Company in Teddington? We undertake all loft conversion work in Teddington right