(46, 'Loft Conversion Twickenham', 'Full Design to Build Service', '<strong>Looking to Convert your Loft in Twickenham?</strong>', 'Loft Conversions Company in Twickenham, South London', '<h1>\n	Twickenham Loft Conversions</h1>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Where is Twickenham Located?&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Looking for a Loft Conversion in Twickenham? We undertake all loft conversion work in Twickenham right from design to build. Contact our team today for a free estimate and site survey.&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;<span style="font-size:22px;">Twickenham is another place I enjoy visiting in my yearly rounds for I love rugby. This affluent Borough lies along River Thames west London, about 10 miles west-southwest of Charing Cross. Since 1965. it is historically part of Middlesex and of the London Borough of Richmond upon Thames.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">As an extensive town center, Twickenham is famous for being the homebase of the rugby union in England. Its historic riverside area is well-known for its 18th-century buildings and pleasure grounds. Three grand period mansions are found in the ground that allow public access. They are: (i) Marble Hill, (ii) Strawberry Hill House, and (iii) York House. No longer around is the mansion belonging to Alexander Pope, 18th-century aphoristic poet. Special mention includes Horace Walpole, the Neo-Gothic prototype man of letter &amp; politician.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Twickenham or Twickers Stadium</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">The famous rugby union stadium in Twickenham is owned and operated by the Rugby Football Union (the RFU) is the second biggest stadium in the U.K. The stadium has been host to test matches for the England national rugby union team, as well as, other rugby union games and has hosted part of the National Football League London Games held in 2016 and 2917 of the American football.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Why live in Twickenham?</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size: 22px;">In the world of sports, Twickenham is synonymous with Rugby Union but for its residents, this south-west London suburb is a peaceful riverside they call home. Located at the sweeping bend in the Thames, the place has London&rsquo;s best selections of quality state schools, a wide array of family homes and a strong sense of community.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Type of Houses in Twickenham&nbsp;</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">In Twickenham, houses are a blend of the Edwardian, Victorian, and later designs homes of the period. There are big detached, semi-detached and terrace varieties of houses, along with periodic purpose-built flats and modern apartments, while along the Montpelier Row, Georgian houses with fine terraces overlook Marble Hill Park. In St Margaret&rsquo;s, an area in the middle of Richmond Bridge and Twickenham Bridge, there is the &ldquo;Trust Grounds&rdquo;, featuring big Victorian homes that are detached and semi-detached. They are found all along the way until the rich large communal gardens of St Peter&rsquo;s, St George&rsquo;s, Ailsa Roads and The Avenue. There are large Victorian houses made of red-brick that are detached or semi-detached along in road in Strawberry Hill and some are in Waldegrave Gardens. Over- looking Twickenham Green and in Second Cross Road are lovely and cozy period cottages.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">In Twickenham is found the most expensive house for sale called the Ferry House. Area of the place measures 6,677sq ft., with eight-bedroom, an outdoor swimming pool and a landscaped garden that overlooks the slipway to Eel Pie Island. The price is a whopping amount of &pound;8.5?million.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Loft Conversion in Twickhenham</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Most houses enjoyed all the space they need from a bespoke loft conversion as houseowners realized the use of loft conversion as one of the most straightforward ways of gaining extra space. Loft conversions is an ideal way to get extra value from your Twickenham premises without extending an inch of the footprint of your home. Considering the roof structure and planning limitations, most houses are suitable for some kind of loft conversion.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/Windsor-avenue-hillingdon.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Homeowners common question asked about conversion</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">&ldquo;Is my Twickenham house suitable for a loft conversion?&rdquo;</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Several factors determine whether your Twickenham loft is suitable for conversion: They are -</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>1. Height of the head</strong> &ndash; It must be about a minimum of 2.2 m so measure from the top of the ceiling joist until the bottom of the ridge timber.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>2. Pitch angle</strong> - The more useable floor area of your loft conversion can have 40&deg; or more to be considered suitable for a conversion.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>3. Any obstacle?</strong> Before any loft conversion plans, consider fixed obstacles found in the area such as chimneys, ventilation pipes and water tanks that need to be considered.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>4. Structure age</strong> &ndash; Houses built before 1960 have more conversion friendly structure than houses built post 1960s.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>5. Shape of loft&rsquo;s end</strong> - Affecting the complexity and floor space calculations are shapes of the ends of the loft like Gable (straight) or Hipped (angled) .</span></p>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Types of loft conversions for Twickenham</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">1. Dormer Loft Conversions</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">A dormer simply extends the existing roof, making loft conversion space in the additional floor space and headroom. An additional space will be provided for loft&rsquo;s limited space or headroom that would make possible conversion.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Although flat roof dormers are unattractive outside, they provide a maximum amount of additional internal space. On the other hand, a conversion of the gable fronted and hipped roof dormers conversion will look much more attractive but they are more complicated and will be more expensive.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_56665.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">2. Mansard Loft Conversions</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">There are 2 slopes in a Mansard roof, the lower slope is vertical at 72 degrees and the top section of the roof is horizontal. An advantage offered by a Mansard roof is maximizing the available space within your loft. Mansards are not often seen in the suburbs and almost certainly require planning permission.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">While this type of roof will give you the maximum amount of space in your loft conversion, it does have a disadvantage as it involves replacing the entire roof the construction that will increase the cost.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_82593.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 300px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size:22px;">3. Velux Loft Conversions &nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">This type of conversion is generally very cost effective as it is is quick, simple and in most cases, &nbsp;it does not require planning permission. Windows of roof light Velux are easily installed and only require at least one of the existing rafters to be trimmed out per window.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Where there is a good amount of headroom or if there are constraints on planning, a Velux type loft conversion works very well for lofts. For example, if you live in a conservation area and there is an extremely limited headroom, then a better option is either a dormer or mansard conversion. There will be disruption or delays while making the conversion even during bad weather since Velux roof lights can be fitter fast and easily.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/velux-loft-conversion-london.jpg" style="width: 800px; height: 600px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Tips to bring down the cost of Loft Conversion in Twickenham</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">1. Raising the height of your roof and adding skylights, windows, as well as. other structural changes will surely add to the cost of your conversion. So, if your standing room is already enough for a habitable space, you could save by limiting the current measurement of your new room.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2. Finalized and sent off planning approval as early as possible. Although not all loft conversions need planning permission for they are covered under permitted development rights that allow the improvement and extension of homes under certain restrictions.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3. It&rsquo;s an economical option if you act as project manager to your loft conversion as you cut your building costs. You will be managing all the tradesmen and setting your own timetable. However, you&rsquo;ll need to be clear on exactly what needs to be done and know what everyone needs to do. That would include management of budget, logistics, and time. You must check all deliveries of materials, deal with contractors and the day-to-day running of the site. You&rsquo;ll also need to be available all the time for key decisions need your presence.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">4. Consider the position of plumbing for it greatly impacts on the cost. The position of plumbing must be directly over the pipework that is below the floor for less work will be required than re-routing plumbing across the house. This way, cost will be cheaper.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">5. Get everything done in writing as soon as you have chosen a builder or loft conversion company, include the work of the architect, and have contract prepared detailing all the work that will be done. If there are materials to be delivered, draw up a contract with your supplier with a confirmed delivery date.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">For all our advice on cutting the cost of your conversion, visit our loft conversion costs and see our services.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Where to get funding for a Loft Conversion?</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Remortgage your property - Funding for a loft conversion is tedious if your capital is not adequate. However, many people get the funds for a loft conversion by remortgaging their current property so your mortgage lender should not have any issue in giving you the money.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">You will be able to remortgage and increase your mortgage for the loft conversion is going to add value to your property. It is a good way to show that your house has increased in value since the last time it was mortgaged. If your house is going down in value than the chances are your mortgage will not be approved.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Apply for a loan &ndash; To finance loft conversion, a loan may turn out cheaper in later estimate and it may be cheaper to apply for a loan. At the onset, remortgaging may even mean lower monthly payments, but after months of payments you will realize that you are paying for more. A home improvement loan is one good reason for applying for a loan. Tell your bank that a loft conversion is the purpose of the loan and they will surely approve it. They prefer a home improvement loan than to buy a new car.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Take out a secured loan - You may also want to consider taking out a secured loan, the rates on these types of loans can sometimes cost more than a normal loan, but the money will be used for a loft conversion that will also improve the value of your home, then the cost pays for itself.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Ask help from your local authority - Your local council may also be able to offer you what is known as home improvement grants. If you can prove that a loft conversion will raise the value of your home, it will be considered as grant for improvement.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">These types of grants are normally offered to families or households on a low income. Local authorities assist homeowners get home improvement loans they may supply you with a builder or tools to carry out the work and they may also pay for the work to be done for you, but by one of their designated builders.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Last words about funding: Trying to get a loan for any purpose is becoming increasingly harder, but if you can prove that you are a good payer, you will surely get funding for your loft. If not you should contact your local authority and ask about improvement loans and whether you will be considered, if you are on a low income and can show you are increasing the value of your home or converting for much needed space, the chances are they will be able to help you.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Conclusion:</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">According to loft conversion companies, loft conversion cost in London is tentatively approximated between the amount of &pound;25,000 &ndash; &pound;40,000 upwards. But there are other factors to consider as the type of conversion. Our company design and build each loft conversion based on the customer&rsquo;s needs and stated budget, but your decision to have lost conversion is a wise one. Get a professional to help you so that you can avoid all the stress that comes in doing a project. Our company is just a click away. Do contact us anytime!</span></p>\n<p>\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 22px;">Some useful links for you to read on before starting your Loft Conversion.</span></strong></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/loft-conversion-ideas-to-choose-from"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Loft Conversion Ideas to Choose From</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://loftconversionlondon.com/marketing/do-you-need-planning-permission-for-your-loft-conversion"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Do you need planning permission for your Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n<p>\n	<a href="https://www.which.co.uk/reviews/loft-conversions/article/loft-conversions/loft-conversions-step-by-step-guide"><span style="font-size: 22px;">Step by Step Guide to Loft Conversion</span></a></p>\n', '', 'Loft Conversion Twickenham | Loft Conversions Company Twickenham                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                ', 'Looking for a Loft Conversion in Twickenham? We undertake all loft conversion work in Twickenham right from design to build. Contact our team today for a free estimate and site survey                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     ', 'Loft Conversion Twickenham', 'loft-conversion-twickenham', NULL, 1, '1', '1', 0, '', '', '2020-06-14'),
(47, 'Loft Conversion Chiswick', 'Full Design to Build Service', 'Looking to Convert your Loft in Chiswick?', 'Loft Conversions Company in Chiswick, West London', '<h1>\n	Chiswick Loft Conversions</h1>\n<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Where is Chiswick located?&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Chiswick is an affluent district filled with trees and greenery that creates a village with comfortable feelings. You will be rubbing elbows with creative professionals and the media in many local shops, when you unwind in some cozy wine bars and eat sumptuous dinner in any of high-end restaurants along Chiswick High Road. As you stroll along the footpath, you will pass by pubs rich in history and picturesque 18th-century homes along Strand-on-the-Green in Thame-side street. You will be artistically satisfied with the Old Master paintings in the Roman-style Chiswick House and appreciate the has wide-spread manicured gardens that families held picnic and used as children&rsquo;s play areas.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">I learned that some of the most outstanding residents in Chiswick included:18th-century English poet Alexander Pope who is popular for his satirical verse, and W. B. Yeats, an Irish poet and one of the foremost figures of 20th-century literature. There was the Italian revolutionary Ugo Foscolo; the Impressionist painter Camille Pissarro, a staunch contributor to both Impressionism and Post-Impressionism; E. M. Forster, English novelist, short story writer, essayist and librettist; and stage director Peter Brook.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Interesting facts about Chiswick</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Several inns of Chiswick have history like (i) the Tabard Inn built by Norman Shaw containing a 96-seat theatre on its ground first floor; (ii) the George and Devonshire Inn; (iii) The Mawson Arms Inn that was a pub split into an ale house and a separate wines and spirits bar; (iv) The &nbsp;Old Packhorse that was constructed built by Nowell Parrwho was a local Fuller&#39;s Brewery architect.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Yearly cheese fairs were held on Dukes Meadows in Chiswick between11th and 18<sup>th</sup> century or around 700 years. Even the name of &quot;Chiswick&quot; comes from an Old English word meaning &quot;cheese farm&quot;.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">For gourmet listen!&nbsp; Chiswick boost of two Michelin star restaurants &ndash; Hedone and The La Trompette, Note that Hedone was recently named as the 60th best restaurant in the world despite the restaurants being just four years in operation.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Points of Interest in Chiswick</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Every visitor must visit these landmarks as an interesting point of interest in Chiswick:</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">1. National Archives &ndash; This enormous library contains over 1,000 years of British history, including the Domesday Book;</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2. Chiswick House &ndash; See an authentic 18th century villa and gardens; and</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3.Tabard Theatre &ndash; The perfect place for you to enjoy a play, musical performance or comedy routine.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Why live in Chiswick?</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Chiswick attracts both families and young professionals due to its incomparable vivacity, its outstanding schools, as well as, an excellent blend of colorful shops. well-stocked pubs, and fancy restaurants. It offers water recreational facilities since Chiswick borders the river. Built in 1729, lavish baroque villa Chiswick House is found amid green open spaces. Lovely Victorian cottages, large sedate Victorian detached houses, listed public buildings, riverside Georgian houses are aligned alongside modern apartments, modern developments, lots of conversions and mansion blocks. The broad range of family homes and its unapparelled vibrancy made Chiswick one of the most popular of London&rsquo;s suburbs in which to buy or rent.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Loft Conversion in Chiswick</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Most Chiswick houses are not new to loft conversion as homeowners understand that they have to decide whether or not to modify your home and create that extra space for office, gym or play area. They are aware that by loft conversions, there unused and dusty attic was transformed to a unique and innovative area for the whole family to use. To do away with the rigor and stress in handling a project, they hired our professional company to do it for them. That&rsquo;s why our experienced team introduced homeowners to the hidden value in your home and helped them deciding the type of loft conversion is suited for the space.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">We assisted them in (1) planning the basic design according to their vision; (2) in applying for planning permission (if needed); and (3) helping to stay within their budget helping get the best value for their money.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_54065.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Why get a Loft Conversion in Chiswick?</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Here are just a few reasons why you shout have as loft conversion.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Enjoy a bigger and more comfy living space</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Make use of a home space that lies idle</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Conversion is the best home improvement for your money</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*A moving expense along cost around &pound;10,000, so you save this amount.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*Avoid the stress in moving to a new house</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">*You make your house more attractive to buyers and add higher value</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>The main types of Loft Conversions in Chiswick</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Every loft conversion are the same, there are certain types of conversions that you can choose from.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">1. Dormer loft conversion has many styles and is categorized as, double, full, L-shaped, rear, and single dormer loft conversions. Compared to other types, the dormer has vertical walls and horizontal ceilings. They could be shaped as flat, hipped, or L-shaped.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_56665.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">2. Mansard loft conversion is best for urban or conversation area for the featured walls on either side are raised as a brickwork. Its roof with the back wall has an inward slope at approx. 70&ndash;72 degrees.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_82593.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 300px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">3. Hip to Gable loft conversion is most suitable for detached or semi-detached homes. The three slanting sides to the roof is then extended to the outside wall where the gable end is built up. The front slop builds up the conversion following completion of rear dormer and Velux windows so there is an extension on both sloping sides.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/temp/full/gallery_soft_36859.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">4. One great choice is a Velux loft conversion that is available if conversion is a smaller loft. You achieve keeping the original style of the roof by installing the Velux windows and roof lights.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/velux-loft-conversion-bedroom.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Choosing your window styles&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Windows play an important role in every loft conversion for they provide the natural light to the loft and they greatly affect the physical appearance from the interior and exterior side. Consider these various window styles you may choose from.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Simple roof lights, or roof windows, are set up into the sloping roof. Made from traditional cast iron, conservation roof lights are more expensive but they are fine options for period buildings.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Also called as vertical windows, dormer windows are placed in the roof and are projected upwards. By providing a standing space within the sloping roof, they can create extra space in the conversion.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><img alt="" src="https://loftconversionlondon.com/images/loft-conversion-edgware-orange-hill2.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 450px;" /></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Standard windows like the gable-end windows are fitted at the building&rsquo;s side into the vertical walls. Their main function is to provide added light into the conversion.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Your chosen styles of window type will depend on several considerations as looking from the view of your home, the property style and the chosen type of your loft conversion.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<strong>Loft Conversion Ideas - Clever Solutions for Your Chiswick Home</strong></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Loft Conversions are the new modern technique to give your old home a fresh smart look. The best loft conversion prospects will assist you with taking advantage of the space in your home. Loft Conversion Chiswick will give you a very much structured, cunningly considered room that will make extra tenable space and consequently, help let lose a bustling family unit. Regardless of whether you&#39;re thinking about a storage room or an additional playing den or a tea- party room Loft Conversion London is your safe bet as a company. It&#39;s an extremely smart option in contrast to moving to another house and could even increase the value of your home.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">After extensive research by our expert designers we found these 5 loft conversion ideas that are currently a big hype in the market -</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>1.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>EMBRACE ITS PROPORTIONS THROUGH COLORS -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">If your plans regarding the loft conversion are not about bigger changes, or you&#39;re settling on two or three little rooms instead of one huge one, exploit the normally comfortable feel offered by little spaces.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">While settling on a color shaded plan &ndash; you truly can&#39;t beat white. It has the ability to cause loft rooms to feel bigger and lighter. Your objective should be to keep it from feeling excessively clinical.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Attempt to combine lighter hues with warm woods and the incidental delicate outfitting in a 