(72, 'Loft Conversion Chelsea', '', '<strong>Are you Looking for your Dream Loft Conversion in Chelsea?</strong>', 'Loft Conversion Company in Chelsea ,Central London', '<h2>\n	<strong>A brief about Chelsea</strong></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">This suburb is a well-known name for smart boutiques &amp; high-end restaurants. Chelsea is located in South West London, surrounded from the south by the River Thames.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Chelsea, is a rich, cosmopolitan district in Central London and famous for its posh residents, with citizens earning three times higher than the national average.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Considered as one of the wealthiest and developed areas, Chelsea has proper facilities of transportation, education, culture and all. Hence, it is quite apparent that this part of London is the preferred location to stay with families.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<strong>Why is Chelsea the right place to live with family?</strong></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">There is no negative fact about living in Chelsea. The locality of the town is superb, and it is increasing. In terms of educational facilities as well, the area has its own place. The borough happens to be one of the preferable choices for many to reside with their families and lead a comfortable life.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">To make life much more accessible and comfortable here, adding extra space is always beneficial at the minimal expanse. It is a wise decision for Chelsea people to go for a loft conversion if they want to maximize the size and value of their houses. Loft conversion saves you from paying a considerable amount of money as loft conversion reshape your existing home into a bigger and better form.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Loft conversion gives you an option to change the layout of your house, and it is much more convenient than moving to another home.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<strong>What should I consider before going for conversion?</strong></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Maybe you&#39;ll want to start by assessing that your loft is suitable for conversion or not. Where most of the houses located in Chelsea are suitable for conversion, there are three major things which should consider before initiation of your project.</span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Internal height measurement -&nbsp; Measure from the top of the ceiling beam to underneath the ridge board should be 2,500mm to suitably convert.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Footprint - As a thumb rule of conversion, including chimney, footprint needs to be 5,500 mm side to side, and 7,500 mm front to back.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Roof pitch - Angle of the roof needs to be measured. Higher pitch level means higher central head.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<strong>Planning permission and building regulations -</strong></h3>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">In most of the loft conversion, planning permission is not usually required unless your transformation is not exceeding any specific limit. It&#39;s best to verify with the local planning department to understand the limitations and rules of conversion.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Also, do not forget to consider whether your conversion is a subject of The Party Wall Act 1996 under which you need to give adjoining owners notice.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	Why choose our services for your conversion work?</h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Being the best and most trusted loft conversion company, we follow specific guidelines for ensuring to serve our clients with best. Our Design and Building services are becoming feasible for most of the residential projects located in Chelsea. The conversion process incorporates architects, quantity surveyors, party wall engineers, structural engineers, building control and our finest and skilled