i>\n</ul>\n<h4>\n	<strong>Planning permission for Dormer conversion</strong> -</h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">It is advisable to take Planning permission for this type of conversion. It helps in maximizing living space within the roof by effectively creating another storey to the property. As this appears in changes to the roof shape and structure, it is highly likely that you will require planning permission from the local authority.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>Hip to Gable Loft Conversion -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">If you have three separate slanting sides on the roof, Hip to gable is the best way for you in maximizing your living space, especially for semi-detached and detached houses.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>Planning permission for Hip to Gable Loft Conversion -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">It is advisable to take Planning permission for this type of conversion. Loft conversion helps in maximizing living space within the roof by effectively creating an added storey to the property. As this occurs in changes of the roof shape and structure, it is highly likely that you will require planning permission from the local authority.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>L Shaped Mansard Loft Conversion&nbsp; -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">L Shaped Mansard Loft Conversion creates a considerable change in the structure of your roof. Mansards conversion usually has a flat roof with the rear sloped at almost 72 degrees, which is a loophole to qualify the shelter as a wall according to planning criteria.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>Planning permission for L Shaped Mansard Loft Conversion&nbsp; -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">It is advisable to take Planning permission for this type of conversion. Loft conversion helps in maximizing living space within the roof by effectively creating an added storey to the property. As this occurs in changes of the roof shape and structure, it is highly likely that you will require planning permission from the local authority.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>Velux Loft Conversion -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">This is one the most versatile type of conversion and best suitable for a wide range of homes, such as semi-detached, detached and terraced properties.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>Planning permission for Velux Loft Conversion</strong> -</h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">It is advisable to take Planning permission for this type of conversion. Loft conversion helps in maximizing living space within the roof by effectively creating an added storey to the property. As this occurs in changes of the roof shape and structure, it is highly likely that you will require planning permission from the local authority.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<strong>Talk to us to know more about us -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Our clients stand above all for us, and we deliver what we promise.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Our previous customers are a spokesperson for us, and we get most of our works by reference.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">With the highest degree of customer satisfaction, we serve our clients with our full potential.</span></p>\n', '', 'Loft Conversion Chelsea | Chelsea Loft Conversions Company                                   ', 'Looking for Loft Conversion in Chelsea? Let us build your dream loft for your Chelsea home. We provide the best Loft Conversions services across Chelsea and Central London. Contact us for a free no-obligation quote.                                 ', 'Loft Conversion Chelsea', 'loft-conversion-chelsea', NULL, 1, '1', '1', 0, '', '', '2020-10-16'),
(73, 'Loft Conversion Fulham', '', '<strong>Are you Looking for your Dream Loft Conversion in Fulham?</strong>', 'Loft Conversions Company in Fulham, West London', '<h1>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Loft conversion in Fulham</strong></span></h1>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">With the population of 87,161 (2011), the city Fulham has a reputation as one of the most sought-after locations in London and has the highest capital values per square foot of prime South West London. Fulham is famous for its exclusive sports, and social club with the waiting list for membership for fifteen years. Also, it typically doesn&#39;t matter if you are not a fan of football, the stadium has a neutral end, where you can enjoy the game no matter what your allegiance.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">People who live across London prefer to come to <em>Fulham</em> to enjoy suburban <em>living</em> within the nation&#39;s capital. The city has been considered an ideal place for families and grown-ups.</span></p>\n<h2>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Why Should I go for the loft conversion in Fulham?</strong></span></h2>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">As we discussed earlier, Fulham is a great and lovely place for living. The city has all the necessary facilities such as education, transportation etc. along with a touch of modernity. A loft conversion is a prudent and worthy way to improve your living space with remarkable benefits.</span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Turn dead space into the usable living area -&nbsp; Moving a house is the hardest and stressful thing to do. If you have a grown-up family or teenagers, rather than shifting, you can turn your unutilized space into something worth. The loft conversion gives you plenty of opportunities and ideas to use your dead place in converting as a living space, entertainment space, kids room, play or guest room. Either you can convert your loft into an office place to increase your productivity and do your work without any outside disturbance.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Increase your property value - This is one of the most significant advantages of having a loft conversion. It simply adds an average of 20% more value into your existing house. It can convert your one-bedroom home into a two room house, which increases the market value simultaneously. It is a great way of return of investment with a guaranteed profit.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>How can I use my loft?</strong></span></h3>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">There are so many options available for using your converted room. Here we are sharing a few most loveable conversion ideas:</span></p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Convert it into a bedroom -&nbsp; If you have a spare room, and have a growing family or teenagers, you can choose to convert your space into a bedroom.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Kids room -&nbsp; If your loft doesn&#39;t have enough headroom, then you can go for converting your loft into a kids bedroom. You can also use this room to store kids stuff such as toys and clothes etc. Plus, extra beds could be built into the walls leaving the floor space open so they can spend some good time with their friends here.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Create a bathroom - If you have enough spare room, you can turn it into a luxurious bathroom. Place a freestanding bath under the slope of the loft, and accomplish your bathroom with attractive usable accessories.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Turn it into a home office - With the increasing work from office culture, having a separate room for work can help you in enhancing your productivity. Incorporate this room with stuff such as files, papers, laptop and with more office stuff.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Create a multipurpose room - A loft conversion gives you plenty of opportunities to utilize your spare room according to your requirement. You can use it as an entertainment room, chill room, storeroom etc. Although if you do not have any planning to use it right now, maybe in future you need it. Hence stay prepared to avoid any last-minute hassle.</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">A place for your hobbies - Most of us miss those days when we get involved in several games or spend some quality time enjoying our hobbies. With passing the time due to responsibilities or lack of enough space slowly, we leave all these things behind. But if you have enough room in your house, you can turn that into a place where you can spend your good time, enjoying what you love to do. Even you can turn this room into an entertainment room by assembling music systems and don&#39;t forget about acoustic mineral woods to avoid noises coming out.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Different types of loft conversion -</strong></span></h3>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">As being one of the trustworthy loft conversion companies across Fulham, we always keep your vision and requirements in mind. Our specialists always suggest the best suitable type of conversion to fulfil your need.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Here we are sharing majorly demanded types of a loft conversion to choose from:</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Rooflight conversion - This conversion generally does not require any alteration or expansion in the existing space. It is the most straightforward add-in window and transforms the attic floor into a comfortable living space. It significantly requires less structural work.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Pros of Rooflight conversion -</strong></span></h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Almost 25% cheaper than other conversion types</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">No major alteration</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">If it gets used smartly can provide plenty of space to use#</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>\n	<strong style="font-size: 22px;">Hip-to-gable conversions -</strong></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">It is one of the most common types of conversion among the semi-detached and detached houses. A <em>hip to gable loft conversion</em> aligns a naturally slanted end roof to create a vertical wall. The process involves removing the sloping roof end and creating a vertical wall.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Pros of Hip-to-gable conversions -</strong></span></h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">It blends perfectly with an existing house</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Aesthetically pleasing</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Modular extension loft conversions -</strong></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">There is always a possibility that your current place is not ideal for conversion. Removing the oldest roof and installing a new one almost adds the floor. In this, ca convert most of the lost areas with ease, and the choices of how to use the additional space are numerous.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Pros of Modular extension loft conversions -</strong></span></h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Give a completely new appearance</span></li>\n	<li>\n		<span style="font-size:22px;">Suitable for the old houses</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Mansard loft conversions -</strong></span></h4>\n<p>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;">Prefered for a terraced house, Mansard loft conversion is useful for adding additional space on your roof, involving replacing the roof slopes with steeper sloping sides.</span></p>\n<h4>\n	<span style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Pros of Mansard loft conversions -</strong></span></h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<span st